# <type>: <subject>
# |<----  Using a maximum of 50 characters  ---->|
# 
# Example commit messages:
# feat: Add user authentication
# fix: Resolve null pointer in TaskController
# docs: Update API documentation
# test: Add integration tests for task creation
# chore: Update gradle dependencies
# refactor: Improve task scheduling logic
# style: Format code according to guidelines
# perf: Optimize database queries
# build: Update gradle configuration
# ci: Add GitHub Actions workflow
#
# Type can be:
#   feat     (new feature)
#   fix      (bug fix)
#   docs     (documentation changes)
#   style    (formatting, missing semicolons, etc; no code change)
#   refactor (refactoring production code)
#   test     (adding tests, refactoring tests; no production code change)
#   chore    (updating build tasks, package manager configs, etc)
#   perf     (performance improvements)
#   build    (changes to build system)
#   ci       (changes to CI configuration)
#
# Subject should:
#   * use imperative, present tense: "change" not "changed" nor "changes"
#   * start with capital letter
#   * not end with a period
#
# Explain what and why below (if needed), not how
# |<----   Try to limit each line to a maximum of 72 characters   ---->|
